subSubSection.paragraph:
Bactroceras

with a large shell diameter (> 
45 mm
), ornamented with transverse striae, and with concavity of septa of 30%; siphuncle tubular, marginal; diameter of siphuncle ⅛ to ¹/7 of the corresponding conch diameter; connecting ring very thin (after 
Aubrechtová 2015
).
